Generated the Scroll Bar developer guide at `docs/generated/scroll-bar.md`. The document covers:

- Creating a ScrollBar using `ScrollBar::New()` and downcasting with `ScrollBar::DownCast()`
- Configuring appearance: thickness, color, corner radius, minimum size, and offset
- Controlling visibility with `ScrollBarVisibility` enum values (Auto, Always, Never)
- Managing scroll position with `SetScrollPosition()`, `UpdateBarSize()`, and `UpdateScrollPosition()`
- Integration with `ScrollView` for automatic scroll bar management

All API examples were verified against the public header (`scroll-bar.h`), UTC tests (`utc-Dali-ScrollBar.cpp`), and sample code (`scrollbar-example.cpp`).
